                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d113">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.007F/87</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Statement Issued to the Press by the Secretary of State,
                        December 27, 1929</hi>
                </head>
                <dateline>
                    <date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-head" calendar="gregorian"
                        when="1929-12-27">December 27, 1929</date>
                </dateline>
                <p>The investigation of the incidents referred to in the article in <hi
                        rend="italic">Harper’s Magazine</hi> has been completed by this Department
                    and it has not revealed any activities on the part of any residents in this
                    country of Italian extraction or on the part of any Italian officials which were
                    directed against this government or against its institutions.</p>
                <p>So far as the dissolution of the Fascist League is concerned, inasmuch as the
                    existence and purposes of that League have been the subject of adverse
                    speculative comment and possible misunderstanding, I am glad to express my
                    appreciation that the League has dissolved itself in the interest of removing
                    those misunderstandings and better relations between this country and Italy.</p>
            </div>
